DOCUMENT();       

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
#           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
#           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
#           "extraAnswerEvaluators.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
"MathObjects.pl",
"AnswerFormatHelp.pl",
"PGcourse.pl",
           );
       
TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.

Context("Numeric");

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;
$p = random(1,4,1);
$m = random(2,3,1);
$d = random(3,7,1);
$c = random(2,$d-1,1);
if ($c == 3 && $d == 4){$d = 5};

$a = "$m*e^$p";
$root = exp(-$c/$d);
$b = round($root*10000)/10000;
$r = round(($root-1)*10000)/100;
$k = round(-$c/$d*10000)/100;
$dec_r = round(($root-1)*10000)/10000;
$dec_k = round(-$c/$d*10000)/10000;


BEGIN_TEXT
Give the starting value ${BITALIC}a,${EITALIC} the growth/decay rate ${BITALIC}r,${EITALIC} and the continuous growth/decay rate ${BITALIC}k.${EITALIC}  If there is exponential is decay, then your growth rates should be entered as negative percents.  For help entering logarithms, see \{ AnswerFormatHelp("logarithms") \}
$BR
$BR
\( \displaystyle Q = $m e^{($p - \frac{$c t}{$d})} \) has:
$BR
$BR
\( a = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}
\{ AnswerFormatHelp("numbers") \}
$BR
\( r = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}$PERCENT (round to the nearest 0.01${PERCENT}) 
\{ AnswerFormatHelp("numbers") \}
$BR
\( k = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}$PERCENT (round to the nearest 0.01${PERCENT})
\{ AnswerFormatHelp("numbers") \}
END_TEXT

ANS(Real("$a")->cmp() );
ANS(Real("$r")->cmp(tolerance=>0.01,tolType=>"absolute") );
ANS(Real("$k")->cmp(tolerance=>0.01,tolType=>"absolute") );


#ANS(num_cmp($a) );
#ANS(num_cmp($r) );
#ANS(num_cmp($k) );


SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR
We can use exponent rules to place this in the form \( ab^t \): $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \displaystyle $m e^{($p- \frac{$c t}{$d})} = $m \cdot \left( e^{$p} \cdot e^{(-$c t)/ $d} \right) = \left( $m e^{$p} \right) \cdot \left( e^{-$c/$d} \right)^t \)
$BR $SPACE $BR


Writing this as \( Q = \left( $m e^{$p} \right) \cdot \left( e^{-$c/$d} \right)^t \), we have:
$BR $SPACE $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ a= $m e^{$p} \ \), $BR $SPACE $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ b= e^{-$c/$d} \approx $b\ \), $BR $SPACE $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ r = b-1 \approx $dec_r \ \) or about $r${PERCENT}, $BR $SPACE $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ k= \ln{b} = \frac{-$c}{$d} \approx $dec_k \ \) or about $k${PERCENT}
$BR
END_SOLUTION


